# Header conventions

## Include guards

Use `CSVI_<MODULE>_<FILE>_H_` (e.g. `CSVI_CSV_READER_H_`, `CSVI_VIEWER_H_`).

## Include order in `.c` files

1. Own module header first
2. System headers (`<stdio.h>`, etc.)
3. Project headers (`"io/csv-reader.h"`, etc.)

## Cross-module paths

Build adds `-I$(top_srcdir)/src/lib`. Always use layer-prefixed paths:

```c
#include "io/csv-reader.h"
#include "layout/types.h"
```

Never use relative paths like `#include "../io/csv-reader.h"`.

## Minimal surface

- Headers expose only the public API; keep helpers `static` in `.c`.
- No ncurses types (`WINDOW`, etc.) in non-`ui/` headers.
- Prefer forward declarations over including heavy headers when a pointer suffices.
